The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, April 12, 2004  Calcutta Column

	Football grounds in the city are in a deplorable state. Even Salt Lakes Yuva Bharati Krirangan is in a shambles. A light shower turns these playgrounds into a slushy, muddy mess. Rainwater, accumulated in puddles, makes it even more dangerous for the players. 
	B.N. Bose, Dum Dum. 
	During a recent visit to SSKM Hospital, I noticed that the sodium vapour lamps on the stretch between the hospital and JL Nehru Road were burning even at noon. This is a criminal waste of electricity on the part of the authorities. 
	Anil Kumar Sen, Ram Chandra Chatterjee Lane. 

